        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-12-07T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-12-07T04:00:00-05:00" n="717" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d717">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/12–749: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Peiping</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clubb</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-12-07T17:00:00+08:00">December 7, 1949—5 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 7—1:37 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2221. French Consul General Breal informs me re Contel 2149, December 1, it is
                    projected he make statement French position to Peiping authorities; action
                    presently being temporarily held up to await clearance from Indochina
                    authorities. Position per international law, foreign armed forces which might
                    try retreat into Indochina would be repulsed or disarmed and interned.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clubb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
